The global on-site oil condition monitoring market is projected to witness substantial growth during the forecast period of 2022 to 2029. The market growth can be attributed to the increasing demand for predictive maintenance strategies in various industries to enhance operational efficiency. On-site oil condition monitoring offers real-time data on the health of oil and machinery, enabling proactive maintenance actions. This helps in reducing downtime, minimizing maintenance costs, and extending the lifespan of equipment. The adoption of on-site oil condition monitoring is expected to surge across industries such as transportation, industrial, oil & gas, energy & power, among others, driving market growth.

